<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Flatpak on Dan Aukes</title><link>https://www.danaukes.com/tags/flatpak/</link><description>Recent content in Flatpak on Dan Aukes</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://www.danaukes.com/tags/flatpak/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Preparation</title><link>https://www.danaukes.com/notebook/ubuntu-setup/01.1-preparation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.danaukes.com/notebook/ubuntu-setup/01.1-preparation/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="things-you-will-need">Things you will need&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>ssh public key&lt;/li>
&lt;li>configuration backup file&lt;/li>
&lt;li>gpg key&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="first-update-apt">First, update apt&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>sudo apt update
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e">#save this for the end&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#75715e"># sudo apt upgrade -y&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="if-a-virtual-machine">If a Virtual machine&lt;/h2>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>
&lt;p>make sure you are a member of the vboxusers and vboxsf groups ^[&lt;a href="https://www.virtualbox.org/manual/ch03.html#usb-implementation-notes">https://www.virtualbox.org/manual/ch03.html#usb-implementation-notes&lt;/a>]&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Multiple Clocks in Ubuntu / Gnome</title><link>https://www.danaukes.com/notebook/multiple-clocks/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.danaukes.com/notebook/multiple-clocks/</guid><description>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>sudo apt install -y gnome-clocks
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>flatpak install -y com.mattjakeman.ExtensionManager
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>flatpak run com.mattjakeman.ExtensionManager
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>click browse tab
search for &amp;ldquo;world clock&amp;rdquo; and select &amp;ldquo;panel world clock&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>quick scripts for openscad</title><link>https://www.danaukes.com/notebook/openscad/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.danaukes.com/notebook/openscad/</guid><description>&lt;pre tabindex="0">&lt;code>color(&amp;#34;red&amp;#34;,1) import(&amp;#34;path/to/your-part.stl&amp;#34;);
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#272822;background-color:#fafafa;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>flatpak run org.openscad.OpenSCAD -o test.png --projection orthogonal test.scad
